This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with semantic segmentation, which is a fundamental task in computer vision. The use of Convolutional Networks (CNNs) and Graphical Models also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as the PASCAL IOU loss function, which could place it in the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the use of novel CNNs for semantic segmentation could also suggest the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
